lenders.loan_because: need budget for Mr.mamat to keep sell his baso food in some place it means not like travelling circus with cart but in real place.
lenders.occupational_info:
Pedagang kaki lima is a large part of our food culture in Indonesia where the seller uses gerobak to ply their food trade. Gerobak is a movable wooden box which contains a hot stove, complete with mini table and chairs in case the consumer wants to eat by the side of the road. It’s like a mini circus magic cart with food

And in case you're wondering how to differentiate the sellers passing by, it's easy. Due to their marketing efforts, I found it hilarious that there are actually different sounds and colours for every gerobak. Take a look at my top three favorite gerobak- Bakso, Bubur Ayam and Nasi Goreng. They come with different knocking sounds, some of them even play cute songs not unlike an advertisement jingle. Funny! Each gerobak also diversifies their design element, in terms of the colour that they use. Nowadays they even decorate their gerobak in all sorts of ways to be more eye-catching

lenders.loan_because:
I like that loans don't have to be huge, and that returns aren't a big deal. I like that these partners are working on an individual (or small group) level. I don't know where this will head in the future, but the philanthropic slant to loaning/investing is interesting, and I fully support this (at this point). Life is not fair, and I want to do what I can. This is a start. 

I like loaning towards education; everyone has a right to more than basic education if they so desire. Cost should not be an impediment towards attaining that. Although I've no clue if the amount I contribute will go towards the sectors I applied them to... I don't mind them going elsewhere too.
